==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unreason
<hw>Un*rea"son</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>reason</ets>.]</ety> <def>Want of reason;
unreasonableness; absurdity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Abbot of Unreason</b></col>. <cd>See <cref>Abbot of
Misrule</cref>, under <er>Abbot</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unreason</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unreason
<hw>Un*rea"son</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref. <ets>un-</ets> +
<ets>reason</ets>.]</ety> <def>To undo, disprove, or refute by
reasoning.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>unreason</qex> the equity of God's proceedings.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unreasonable</ent>⟦br⟧
